{
  "texts": [
    "The neighborhood of v ∈ V is denotedAdj(v) = {w ∈ V | {v, w} ∈ E}.",
    "The degree of v, denoted d v, is the car- dinality of its neighborhood, that is, d v = |Adj(v)|.",
    "If w ∈ Adj(v), we say that w is adjacent to v. Given S ⊂ V, the subgraph of G induced by S is denoted G[S], if G[S] is a complete subgraph, then S is called a clique.",
    "A clique of size k is denoted k-clique.",
    "A clique is maximal if it is nota proper subset (different from ∅ and the set itself) of any other clique."
  ]
}